      "raw_text": "Strikers today are claiming that\nfrom the small number who walked\nout with them two weeks ago addi-\nlions have been made until now the\nnumber is swelled to 70. Edward\nMcMorrow, executive officer in\ncharge here, today expressed con-\nfidence of winning. He said that\nthe spirit at all the union meetings\nhe has attended has been strongly\nin favor of the strikers. But the\ncity council, | should Judge\" said\nMcMorrow. lis hand and glove with\nthe Washington Water Power Co.\"\n\n\nMcMorrow's outburst followed a\nreport of the action by the council\nlast night in refusing to take up\nfor immediate consideration reso-\nluton to propose arbitration Of the\ntrouble."
